   {:e #blake3 "590f6fd74144acfdd3f0052a1910e08866010f1a0faa9032bd26bbe8097957b3" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-70d661f9308d00a5; Session entity: :task/t-378b7136; Model Management; Session entity: :task/t-a707579b; Vector Space Consistency; Session entity: :recon/trace-119435f2d3d13f74; Session entity: :task/t-44e834d1; Embedder Selection; Session entity: :task/t-7fd2900f\nADR-EMBEDDING-001: Model Management — model files stored at ~/.braid/models/<model-name>/ with project-local override at .braid/models/. Download via explicit 'braid model download' command (no auto-download — respects user agency and avoids surprise network access). The kernel never performs IO (C8). The CLI loads model bytes and passes to Embedder::from_bytes(). Alternatives rejected: (1) auto-download at first use — violates offline-first principle, breaks behind firewalls, (2) bundle model in binary — 30MB binary bloat, (3) cloud inference API — latency + cost + network dependency. Rationale: the embedding model is a policy-layer artifact (like a tokenizer or schema), not a kernel artifact. Different projects may use different models. The model path is discoverable, not configurable — convention over configuration. Traces to: C8 (kernel is IO-free), ADR-FOUNDATION-013 (policy as datoms).; INV-EMBEDDING-004: Vector Space Consistency — all embedding datoms within a single store MUST be produced by the same embedder type. Mixed vector spaces (e.g., some datoms from HashEmbedder, others from model2vec Embedder) produce meaningless cosine similarity. Falsification: any store where cosine_similarity is computed between an embedding from HashEmbedder and an embedding from Embedder without re-embedding migration. Verification: (1) Unit test: create innate concepts with hash embedder, create observation with model embedder, verify concept assignment produces cosine near 0 (cross-space meaningless). (2) After re-embedding migration, cosine produces meaningful values. Traces to: SEED.md S4 (Design Commitment 2 — content-addressable identity requires consistent embedding space).; ADR-EMBEDDING-002: Embedder Selection — the CLI resolves the best available embedder at startup. If model files exist at the discovery path, construct Embedder::from_bytes() (model2vec). If absent, fall back to HashEmbedder. The embedder is constructed ONCE and shared across all commands in a session. On embedder type change (hash→model or model→hash), the system detects the mismatch via :concept/embedder-type datoms and triggers re-embedding migration of existing concept centroids. Alternatives rejected: (1) always require model — breaks zero-dependency init, (2) always use hash — insufficient semantic quality (DOGFOOD-3 scored 5.3/10), (3) let user choose — unnecessary ceremony, auto-detection is deterministic. Rationale: graceful degradation is a first-principles requirement (INV-EMBEDDING-003). The system MUST work without any model file. The model makes it BETTER but is not required. Traces to: INV-EMBEDDING-003 (graceful degradation), ADR-FOUNDATION-015 (Observer Formalism)." :op :assert}
